Iska Main Concept

Ye method tree ko Depth First (DFS style) me banata hai.

Matlab:

➡️ Pehle root
➡️ Fir pura left subtree
➡️ Fir pura right subtree

Input ka format
1 2 -1 -1 3 -1 -1

-1 means NULL/no node.

Kaise kaam karta hai
Step-by-step

Input = 1

Tree:

1

Now function left child banane chala gaya.

Input = 2

    1
   /
  2

Ab 2 ka left child.

Input = -1

Means no node.

Ab 2 ka right child.

Input = -1

Means no node.

So 2 complete.

Ab recursion wapas 1 pe aayega.

Now right child.

Input = 3

    1
   / \
  2   3
Important Concept

Ye method recursion stack use karta hai.

Tree creation happens:

Root → Left → Left → Left ...

Then backtracking hoti hai.

Isliye ise DFS-based creation bol sakte ho.


import java.util.Scanner;

class Node {
    int data;
    Node left, right;

    Node(int value) {
        data = value;
        left = right = null;
    }
}

public class Main {

    static Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

    static Node BinaryTree() {

        int x;
        x = sc.nextInt();

        if (x == -1)
            return null;

        Node temp = new Node(x);

        temp.left = BinaryTree();

        temp.right = BinaryTree();

        return temp;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Node root = BinaryTree();

        System.out.println("Binary Tree Created");
    }
}



